snippet.textDisplay: First off, as a life long fan (F1, Can-am, Indy, etc), I'm so glad they went back to, and are sticking with the iconic "McLaren Orange"!!! Secondly, I'm not naive enough to think they are going out and winning a bunch of races and the constructors title this year, however, with the groundwork being laid, and the wholesale changes in 2021, I think (hope!!)  that they won't be fighting for 4th in the constructors race, and 6th on the track, behind Mercedes, Ferrari, and Red Bull. I believe Carlos and Lando, both, can consistently fight for podiums, and McLaren can take it to the "Big 3"!!! GOOD LUCK LANDO, CARLOS, AND THE WHOLE MCLAREN TEAM!!!! Give em hell in 2020!!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Team Line-up at management, staff as well as driver level looking confident and hopeful for the upcoming season 2020 after a long winter of hard work. All these efforts will be put to the test during the next few weeks in Barcelona at pre-season testing where we'll get a slight idea on how good the MCL35 is compared to it's rivals. Once the racing starts at the GP Australia 2020, there will be nowhere to hide and McLaren's true colors will reveal themselves to the world.... Speaking of colors: hopefully the papaya will kept at a minimum or disappear giving way to the black-silver colors next year 2021 as McLaren rejoins Mercedes to form the McLaren-Mercedes team in the years to come. The black-silver colors stand for the glory days at McLaren, especially during the 1998 &1999 as well as 2007 & 2008 seasons.
Soundtrack Music in background (4:27 - 5:27 Min): anybody know the name of the music used ? Sounds like music by The Crystal Method....

snippet.textDisplay: I'm a German Haas fan who loved Ferrari and Arrows as a kid, but I think in general, McLaren were always the prettiest cars with the most legendary drivers, no matter if 60s with Bruce himself, 70s with Fittipaldi, Maas and Hunt, 80s with Lauda, Senna and Prost or 90s/00s with Häkkinen and Coulthard, except late 00s/10s era which I didnt like. Since 2018 I think the true McLaren spirit is back and with those amazing cars and drivers I wish them all the best! Time for some podiums for Lando!
snippet.textOriginal: I'm a German Haas fan who loved Ferrari and Arrows as a kid, but I think in general, McLaren were always the prettiest cars with the most legendary drivers, no matter if 60s with Bruce himself, 70s with Fittipaldi, Maas and Hunt, 80s with Lauda, Senna and Prost or 90s/00s with Häkkinen and Coulthard, except late 00s/10s era which I didnt like. Since 2018 I think the true McLaren spirit is back and with those amazing cars and drivers I wish them all the best! Time for some podiums for Lando!
